title: Nice mandir
review: this is a nice mandir. Temples are always a nice place to visit. Not so famous but still worth a visit.

title: Another must visit place.
review: People who will visit Ajmer should visit this place. Very precious and  religious place to visit. many people everyday gathered there.

title: Nice
review: Anted ki Mata  temple is nice. this is beautiful Jain temple. this temple is attractive in tourist must go

title: Jain Temple
review: This Jain temple reflects the traditional culture and saints of the Jain Digamber Sect.The temple showcases numerous chhatris and chanutras while the detailed paintings,carvings and other sculptures over the cenotaphs symbolize the rich tradition and culture of Jain Community.

title: Very new infra
review: This place is highly maintained. This is new temple. many families come here and pray. Very peaceful place.

title: Good place...
review: Very religious temple. This temple is newly built so it is well maintained. Because it is new so few people are came here.

title: Religious
review: Anted ki mata temple is nice religious place of Ajmer. This is very nice jain temple of Ajmer.must see.

title: Can be skipped
review: Anted ki Mata Temple is not a very famous tourist place in Ajmer village & hence can be skipped if you are on a tight schedule.

title: Did not put aesthetic purposes
review: Nothing special. The temple is not so old, but already a veteran – probably because of the fact that it is actively used. Even exists a special festival dedicated to the temple, or generally to Jain religion and its branches, one of which is presented by the  "зarishioners" of this temple. Unlike other Jain temples, its creators did not set out aesthetic purposes. Well, or only embodied unsuccessfully or unsuccessfully the general concept.

title: Old beautiful place
review: Very old temple in the vicinity of Ajmer which is very much famous among locals. Peaceful place with small crowd.

title: mata temple
review: Peace, Divine, Spiritual, l and have no words to explain.

title: Used to be a decent place for picnic, now avoid
review: Nothing spectacular. An open space with some common rides for children. There is a temple too. Become scenic during rains, else nothing much to see here. Avoid...

title: A Nice Temple
review: Anted ki Mata is a Jain temple of Digambar sect. The temples reflects the traditional culture of Jain digambar sect. There are numbers of Chhatris and Chabutaras in temple. Painting and Carvings are attractive. A nice visit.
